<div id="review_126374728" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/126374728" />
    <a title="Jessica" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3283298-jessica"><img alt="Jessica" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1572125481p2/3283298.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/126374728?book_show_action=true">Oct 15, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jessica" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jessica" href="/user/show/3283298-jessica">Jessica</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3283298-jessica?shelf=01-hall-of-fame">01-hall-of-fame</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3283298-jessica?shelf=0-faves">0-faves</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3283298-jessica?shelf=27-contemporary-ya">27-contemporary-ya</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3283298-jessica?shelf=04-made-me-cry">04-made-me-cry</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3283298-jessica?shelf=26-love-the-writing">26-love-the-writing</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3283298-jessica?shelf=23-aussie-reading-challenge">23-aussie-reading-challenge</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer126374728" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10178912701036098509"><br/>And yet again, another one of Melina Marchetta’s novels leaves me utterly breathless!<br/><br/>Alright guys, buckle up, this is going to get sappy. :)<br/><br/>When I started reading The Piper’s Son I was a little confused, I had trouble keeping up with who was related to whom and I had a hard time finding my way back into the story. I already started to panic and was worried that I might not feel the love this time but I told myself to be patient because so far, it had always started out this way for me with March</span>
  <span id="freeText10178912701036098509" style="display:none"><br />And yet again, another one of Melina Marchetta’s novels leaves me utterly breathless!<br /><br />Alright guys, buckle up, this is going to get sappy. :)<br /><br />When I started reading The Piper’s Son I was a little confused, I had trouble keeping up with who was related to whom and I had a hard time finding my way back into the story. I already started to panic and was worried that I might not feel the love this time but I told myself to be patient because so far, it had always started out this way for me with Marchetta’s novels. At first I’m like "hmm, I don’t get what all the fuss is about" but then, all of the sudden, it hits me like a sledgehammer and I’m caught up in the story to the point that I simply can’t put the book down. And of course, that’s exactly what happened again. <br /><br />I honestly don’t know how to explain this but Marchetta has this way of letting her characters do these small acts of kindness which may seem insignificant to others, but they always hit me with such force that it knocks the breath right out of me and I find myself bawling my eyes out. It’s not like in all those fantasy novels where it’s all about a love so strong that you would happily suffer in hell for all eternity if it would save the life of your beloved. No, what Marchetta shows us is the real thing. Honest and raw love. Love between siblings, love between parent and child, love between friends and love between lovers and she doesn’t only show us, she makes us <i>feel</i> it. IMO she does that in a way like no other author can.<br /><br />Her characters are not perfect, they are perfectly <i>flawed</i> and she doesn’t wrap up her stories with a pretty little bow in the end because that’s not how it usually goes in real life. Her characters, her stories, everything about Melina Marchetta’s novels just feels <i>real</i>. <br /><br />Thanks to Nic for sending this book over to Germany and thanks to Olivia for lending it to me.<br /><br />#2 Aussie YA reading challenge. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10178912701036098509" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


