    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_205160016" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/205160016" />
    <a title="Laura" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4844873-laura"><img alt="Laura" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1299680097p2/4844873.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/205160016?book_show_action=true">Sep 04, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laura" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laura" href="/user/show/4844873-laura">Laura</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer205160016" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2762173365795414692"><br/>My love affair with Melina Marchetta continues! :D<br/><br/>Her words, style, and voices make my heart beat faster, stomach drop and twist, and head whirl with thoughts and memories. The tone and feel of her words just fit right in my heart. Her stories seem to pulse with this coiled intensity—a gritty beat that creeps up on me, sticks in my gut, and makes me smile, laugh or cry. Just when I think the sadness is going to overcome me, she throws in a jab of sly humor that makes me laugh out loud. I just lo</span>
  <span id="freeText2762173365795414692" style="display:none"><br />My love affair with Melina Marchetta continues! :D<br /><br />Her words, style, and voices make my heart beat faster, stomach drop and twist, and head whirl with thoughts and memories. The tone and feel of her words just fit right in my heart. Her stories seem to pulse with this coiled intensity—a gritty beat that creeps up on me, sticks in my gut, and makes me smile, laugh or cry. Just when I think the sadness is going to overcome me, she throws in a jab of sly humor that makes me laugh out loud. I just love how she talks to us. <br /><br />Sometimes it takes a bit for me to warm up and trust someone, but once you are in my heart you stay there—that is true in life and my fiction. It took me awhile to warm up to Georgie’s voice, but believe me—once I did, she slid right in, snuggled up to my heart and squeezed the hell out of it! Georgie’s story will forever have a place in my heart. The Mackee family is a lot to handle, but once they capture your heart—they are in there! <br /><br />Tom, on the other hand, had me at his first scene in Saving Francesca. He makes me smile just saying his name. I love how we get to know Tom through his relationships with his family, friends, music, and memories. Marchetta paints a sad, broken picture of a young man lost in grief, but starting to reach out. How Tom feels about the women in his life will make you swoon and “awww”. The boy could be the sweetest thing I have come across in young adult literature! I LOVE Thomas Mackee! :)<br /><br />Truth be told though, this book had my heart with two lines.<br /><br />“Sisters and daughters come second in this family, Tom. They always have.” <br /><br />“Wives can replace their husbands, Georgie, her aunt once told her. But sisters can’t replace their brothers.”<br /><br />All my time reading in this world, I have never come across these themes in print. Never said so loud and clear. Melina Marchetta just made me a fan for life. :)<br /><br />Please pick up Piper’s Son and see what she pokes, rattles, and shakes free from your soul.<br /><br />See what she does to your heart.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2762173365795414692" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

